{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_018PFQznJWjKNPh5pviJ1wW8","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have a comprehensive picture of the RabbitMQ cluster's current state. Let me compile a migration plan:\n\n**Current State:**\n- **Version:** RabbitMQ 3.12.14 on Erlang 25.3.2.15 (3.12 series, out of support)\n- **Image:** rabbitmq:3.12-management\n- **Cluster:** 3-node all-disk cluster (rabbitmq-0, rabbitmq-1, rabbitmq-2), all healthy\n- **Plugins enabled:** rabbitmq_prometheus, rabbitmq_peer_discovery_k8s, rabbitmq_management\n- **Configuration:** Three virtual hosts (`/`, `/app`, `/ops`) with three users (`admin`, `app-user`, `ops-user`) having appropriate permissions, plus two durable classic queues (`app-queue` and `ops-queue`) with high-availability policies applied.\n- **Feature Support:** All RabbitMQ 3.12 features are enabled, but I need to account for significant breaking changes ahead—the `ha-all` policy and classic mirrored queues are deprecated in 3.13 and removed entirely in 4.0, so any upgrade path from 3.12 requires careful planning around queue migration strategies.\n- **Erlang Version:** Moving to 3.13 means upgrading from Erlang 25 to 26, which the management image should handle automatically.\n- **Migration Strategy:** Before upgrading to 4.0, I need to convert the classic queue on `/app` to a quorum queue, remove the deprecated `ha-all` policy, and ensure all feature flags are enabled post-upgrade to 3.13.\n- **Upgrade Path:** The supported route is 3.12 → 3.13 via rolling update, then 3.13 → 4.0 only after feature flags are fully enabled.\n\nNow I'll draft the migration plan document.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":391,"cache_read_input_tokens":37080,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":391},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"stand